1- The first thing we do, is name/ DNS resolution.
getaddrinfo, translates google.com to an IP address like xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx before we get to the socket.

2- We initilize the raw socket
3- we build the ICMP packet (echo request)
4- send packet - we then sendto fd which sends it to the kernel.
5- we then receive the reply - recvfrom, we get the echo reply back from the kernel
6- We then parse the reply, we extract TTL sequence and verify the packet
7 - we calculate the RTT between the echo and the reply requsts
8 - we run a loop with 1s interval
9 - we then print stats.

